comments: Leonard (POR) rolls to the basket and makes incidental contact with Iguodala (GSW).
LAR shows Leonard (POR) and Iguodala (GSW) engage and disengage during the rebound.
McCollum (POR) briefly places two hands on Green (GSW) in the post but the contact is marginal.
Lillard (POR) briefly places an arm around Iguodala (GSW) going around the screen, but he immediately releases.
Turner (POR) makes marginal contact with Green (GSW) that does not restrict his FOM.
Leonard (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Thompson (GSW) and does not deliver contact.
[Detectable with stop watch] Curry (GSW) is in the lane without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.

RAR and RLB show Green (GSW) maintains his legal guarding position as he jumps to the side of Lillard (POR) during his jump shot attempt.  Green would avoid making contact, but Lillard jumps to his side to create the marginal contact.
Thompson (GSW) makes incidental contact with Turner (POR) during the rebound and does not affect his ability to get to the ball.
Leonard (POR) places a hand/arm to the front of Curry (GSW) during the drive but the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Iguodala (GSW) and McCollum (POR) engage and disengage off ball during the inbound.
Leonard (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Iguodala (GSW) and does not deliver contact.
Looney (GSW) cleanly deflects the ball away from McCollum (POR).
Looney (GSW) does not beat McCollum (POR) to the spot, but he does not initiate and deliver contact and the contact is marginal.
Leonard (POR) makes incidental arm contact with Green (GSW) during the rebound.
Thompson (GSW) makes incidental arm contact with McCollum (POR) during the rebound.
Leonard (POR) makes incidental contact with Thompson (GSW) during the rebound.
[Observable in enhanced video] Lillard (POR) switches his pivot foot before the release of his dribble.
Thompson (GSW) commits a take foul on Lillard (POR).
Iguodala (GSW) makes marginal contact with Lillard (POR) on the perimeter before cleanly stripping the ball.
